{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.44",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 44,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 44 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:1",
      "text": "Let us now praise men of renown and our fathers in their generation.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:2",
      "text": "The Lord hath wrought great glory through his magnificence from the beginning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:3",
      "text": "Such as have borne rule in their dominions, men of great power, and endued with their wisdom, shewing forth in the prophets the dignity of prophets,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:4",
      "text": "And ruling over the present people, and by the strength of wisdom instructing the people in most holy words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:5",
      "text": "Such as by their skill sought out musical tunes, and published canticles of the scriptures.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:6",
      "text": "Rich men in virtue, studying beautifulness: living at peace in their houses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:7",
      "text": "All these have gained glory in their generations, and were praised in their days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:8",
      "text": "They that were born of them have left a name behind them, that their praises might be related:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:9",
      "text": "And there are some, of whom there is no memorial: who are perished, as if they had never been: and are become as if they had never been born, and their children with them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:10",
      "text": "But these were men of mercy, whose godly deeds have not failed:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:11",
      "text": "Good things continue with their seed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:12",
      "text": "Their posterity are a holy inheritance, and their seed hath stood in the covenants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:13",
      "text": "And their children for their sakes remain for ever: their seed and their glory shall not be forsaken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:14",
      "text": "Their bodies are buried in peace, and their name liveth unto generation and generation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:15",
      "text": "Let the people shew forth their wisdom, and the church declare their praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:16",
      "text": "Henoch pleased God, and was translated into paradise, that he may give repentance to the nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:17",
      "text": "Noe was found perfect, just, and in the time of wrath he was made a reconciliation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:18",
      "text": "Therefore was there a remnant left to the earth, when the flood came.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:19",
      "text": "The covenants of the world were made with him, that all flesh should no more be destroyed with the flood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:20",
      "text": "Abraham was the great father of a multitude of nations, and there was not found the like to him in glory, who kept the law of the most High, and was in covenant with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:21",
      "text": "In his flesh he established the covenant, and in temptation he was found faithful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:22",
      "text": "Therefore by an oath he gave him glory in his posterity, that he should increase as the dust of the earth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:23",
      "text": "And that he would exalt his seed as the stars, and they should inherit from sea to sea, and from the river to the ends of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:24",
      "text": "And he did in like manner with Isaac for the sake of Abraham his father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:25",
      "text": "The Lord gave him the blessing of all nations, and confirmed his covenant upon the head of Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:26",
      "text": "He acknowledged him in his blessings, and gave him an inheritance, and divided him his portion in twelve tribes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.44.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 44:27",
      "text": "And he preserved for him men of mercy, that found grace in the eyes of all flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
